We've developed a page blueprint *without* index page setting using disable-index-page="true".

Now, when someone edits the page template from the administration an index page is automatically created.

I think the problem is

*DefaultContentBlueprintManager*

{code}
ContentTemplateRef indexPageTemplateRef = object.getIndexPageTemplateRef();
        if (indexPageTemplateRef != null)
        {
            ContentTemplateRefAo childAo = contentTemplateRefManager.internalUpdateAo(indexPageTemplateRef);
            childAo.setContentBlueprintIndexParent(ao);
            childAo.save();
        }
{code}

* indexPageTemplateRef  is never null, as it always falls back to "com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-create-content-plugin:default-index-template"
* also object.isIndexDisabled() returns false, even if it should return true instead
* I tried to circumvent it through manually deleting the index page using ContentTemplateRefManager, but unfortunately this is not accessible through OSGi

