h4.Steps to Reproduce:
- Create a page in Confluence
- Add a JIRA macro to the page with some issues in it
- Add a Change History Macro to the page
  
h4.Expected Results:
JIRA issue macro should keep the same look and there should be not changes to it just like the screen shot below:
!wordwrap1.png!
h4.Actual Results:
Following is added to the page:
{code}
 .aui td     { white-space:nowrap; }
{code}
And because of this, there will be a scrollbar under the JIRA macro and you can't see everything without having to scroll.
!wordwrap2.png!

h4.Workaround:
Adding the following to {{Confluence Admin > Stylesheet}}, will help with the view:
{code}
.aui td {
white-space: normal !important;
}
{code}

Some index updates get lost when using Oracle Database with Real Application Clusters (RAC):
{code}
enqueue Newly enqueued entry in journal [main_index] has an ID [423954] that should have been higher than the journal state store's most-recent-id [423965]. it is likely that this node's journal state store is corrupt.
{code}

The reason for this error is that [sequences in Oracle RAC|https://docs.oracle.com/cd/B28359_01/server.111/b28286/statements_6015.htm#SQLRF01314] are not sequential by default.

*Workaround*

# Change SEQ_JOURNAL_ENTRY_ID sequence to be ordered: {{ALTER SEQUENCE SEQ_JOURNAL_ENTRY_ID ORDER;}}
# Rebuild indexes.

