Currently, the Drag-n-Drop box on a page's Attachments brings up a nice progress bar for all of the attachments dragged in during an upload, but using the "Choose File" old fashioned workflow in a modern browser doesn't provide any feedback (outside of the browser's progress bar, which is mediocre at best on a good day).

It would be nice if, at least in modern browsers, the Choose File workflow could be hijacked to provide some sort of feedback for file upload, especially since it's hard to tell what's going on when uploading a very large file (did my network crap out? did my Confluence server go down?)

